Hi,

On Thu, Mar 13, 2003 at 03:59:38PM +0000, Ceri Storey wrote:
> On Thu, Mar 13, 2003 at 03:54:36PM +0100, Oliver Bandel wrote:
> > Hello,
> > 
> > is it possible to add a Reply-To Header-entry to the
> > mailinglist-mails?
> 
> What's wrong with group-reply?


Ok, I have looked around a littlebid.

Group-Reply means answering to list AND via PM.
So this means sending the mail twice.

The correct solutions seems to be list-reply.
It's, what I have to configure (setting a list
of possible List-mailadresses, to match against,
when using mutt-mailer).


But, btw: many people have set their Reply-To-
Field in their Mailadress, and when a mail goes
to them at the privat-address, I often get
the question, if this was intended, or if the
answer should go to the list directly.
(why?)


Ciao,
   Oliver

